.TH "efi_capsule_setup_info" 9 "efi_capsule_setup_info" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
efi_capsule_setup_info \- obtain the efi capsule header in the binary and setup capsule_info structure
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" efi_capsule_setup_info
.BI "(struct capsule_info *cap_info "  ","
.BI "void *kbuff "  ","
.BI "size_t hdr_bytes "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cap_info" 12
pointer to current instance of capsule_info structure
.IP "kbuff" 12
a mapped first page buffer pointer
.IP "hdr_bytes" 12
the total received number of bytes for efi header
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Platforms with non-standard capsule update mechanisms can override
this __weak function so they can perform any required capsule
image munging. See \fBquark_quirk_function\fP for an example.
